			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would first like to point out the Elemental Essence of Fire walkthrough on the Offical 1.5 Epic Walkthrough is unclear and poorly worded. What does "Hits for 2000" and then a few lines later says "Hits for 1400" entail? This makes absolutely no sense. 
<br />

<br />
Tonight I had a first hand look at what happens now with the Fire Essence spawn. 
<br />

<br />
I turned in my Corrosive Solution into Gnapp Guinders. I then said "ready" and he began to walk back into the area where Targin (named ogre) is. That would be the little doored area to the right of where Gnapp is originally stationed. Gnapp wanders back there and then the Elemental Essence of Fire spawns, and walks past Gnapp and into the lava. The Essence goes all the into the lava and swims to the left through the underwater tunnel to a safe room with no lava damage. The AE described below most likely isn't avoidable because of the rooms tiny size. You can NOT cast on him while he wanders to back area. The Essence IS <span style="font-weight: bold">rooted</span> to this spot. 
<br />

<br />
He cast both spells listed under the Walkthrough, but in addition those two he cast this: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3768&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Infernal Flames</a>. My warrior was defensive and was hit for max around 850. Essence may have been triple or quading, but we are not completely sure. Slowable is unknown because he killed our slowers too quickly. 
<br />

<br />
It should also be noted that this attempt was a failure because of nonexistent information on the present Walkthrough's behalf. Gnapp did not respawn after failure, and I am assuming a 2 hour respawn on him. Since the fix of the Essence on the 19th, we can probably assume many things were changed.
<br />

<br />
Please for everyone's sake, take head of this post and make the necessary changes in the Walkthrough to adjust for the lack of clarification.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.atomicrhino.net/steve/nellryn-1.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
