			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did this with 14-15 Tacvi level people, was no problem.  Bard is good idea to resist the AE.  AE rampage is very small range, so have melees fight at maximum melee range, have casters lev up and stand high on walls to avoid it.  Elemental itself doesn't hit too hard (around 800 on defensive warrior max).
<br />

<br />
Desolate Summoned (or Destroy) is the mage nuke of choice.  Landed full damage for me, as did malosinia on 3rd cast.  Fight was maybe 45 seconds with that size raid.
<br />

<br />
Protect vs the AE and its pretty standard fight.   Gnapp was buggy for me on 3 attempts to activate this however, so beware.  Other then that set up as people mention above.
<br />

<br />
Fin</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
